{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Ground services readiness orchestrator - ACU, GPU, wheels chocks",
        "tags": ["readiness", "ground"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 of flight AF84 has been assigned gate A1. Report the readiness of ground services at the gate.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
model_name = "gpt-5.4-mini" # "claude-sonnet-4-6" # "claude-haiku-4-5"
    },
    "max_iterations": 50000,
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200,
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at the San Francisco International Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """ 
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "ground_readiness",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I check and report all ground services readiness statuses at the gate:
air conditioning unit readiness status (acu_readiness_status),
ground power unit readiness status (gpu_readiness_status),
and wheels chocks readiness status (wheels_chocks_readiness_status).
When called with aircraft_type and gate_id, I return all three statuses.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                 
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Gate id assigned to the aircraft."
                        },   
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "ACU readiness status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "GPU readiness status."
                        },   
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of reporting ground services readiness at the gate.
When called, you ALWAYS check ALL THREE ground services readiness statuses in
sequence and return all three results together in a single response.

Proceed as follows:

STEP 1 - Validate inputs
  - Confirm aircraft_type and gate_id are available.
  - If either is missing, call TrackerAPI to retrieve them.
  - If still missing, ask the user and wait.

STEP 2 - Check ACU readiness
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_acu_setup with:
      aircraft_type, gate_id.
  - Wait for response.
  - Store acu_readiness_status.
  - Call TrackerAPI and log acu_readiness_status.

STEP 3 - Check GPU readiness
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_gpu_setup with:
      aircraft_type, gate_id.
  - Wait for response.
  - Store gpu_readiness_status.
  - Call TrackerAPI and log gpu_readiness_status.

STEP 4 - Check wheels chocks readiness
  - Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_setup with:
      aircraft_type, gate_id.
  - Wait for response.
  - Store wheels_chocks_readiness_status.
  - Call TrackerAPI and log wheels_chocks_readiness_status.

STEP 5 - Return combined readiness report
  Provide the ground services readiness summary:
  ***************************************
  * Ground services readiness summary   *
  ***************************************
  ** aircraft type                  **: [aircraft_type]
  ** gate id                        **: [gate_id]
  ** ACU readiness status           **: [acu_readiness_status]
  ** GPU readiness status           **: [gpu_readiness_status]
  ** wheels chocks readiness status   **: [wheels_chocks_readiness_status]

NOTE 1: Always return ALL THREE statuses even if one or more is 'not ready'.
Do not stop early if one status is 'not ready' — complete all three checks
and report all results.
NOTE 2: Always proceed through ALL THREE steps regardless of the result from
any individual step. If a step returns an error string, record the error
as the status value and continue to the next step. Never abort early.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},  

            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools": [
                "TrackerAPI",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_acu_setup",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_gpu_setup",  
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_setup", 
            ]
        },

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "aircraft_type": {"type": "string", "description": "Aircraft type."},         
                        "gate_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Gate id."},     
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."},   
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "GPU readiness status."},      
                        "acu_readiness_status": {"type": "string", "description": "ACU readiness status."},     
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },    
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_readiness.aircraft_ground_readiness.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
